&gt; 
&gt; now, it is hard for me to see &#39;start&#39; and &#39;stop&#39; as values of 
&gt; the &#39;currentactivity&#39; property. if anything, it looks like a 
&gt; masquerade of the RPC equivalent of posting to the 
&gt; VirtualEnvironment entity with the pair &#39;action=start&#39;. 
What happens if a client sends &#39;start&#39; twice? In a state transition diagram,
that would be fairly easy to describe the desired behavior. In an &#39;action
oriented&#39; approach, you&#39;d have to special case that to prevent multiple
initializations/etc.
